---
description: Establishes comprehensive security practices including Spring Security implementation, proper authentication mechanisms, input validation, OWASP compliance, and audit logging to protect applications from common vulnerabilities and unauthorized access.
globs: **/src/main/java/com/shs/b2bm_service_order/security/*.java
alwaysApply: true
---
- Implement Spring Security for authentication and authorization
- Use proper password encoding with BCryptPasswordEncoder
- Implement proper CORS configuration for cross-origin requests
- Include CSRF protection for non-GET requests
- Use JWT or OAuth2 for stateless authentication when appropriate
- Implement proper role-based access control with @PreAuthorize
- Secure sensitive endpoints with appropriate authorization checks
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs to prevent injection attacks
- Use HTTPS in production environments
- Implement proper session management
- Follow OWASP Top 10 security guidelines
- Include security headers in HTTP responses
- Implement rate limiting for sensitive endpoints
- Use secure cookies with HttpOnly and Secure flags
- Keep dependencies updated to avoid security vulnerabilities
- Implement proper logging for security events
- Use security auditing for critical operations